This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning, specifically on the topic of few-shot learning using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the development of novel models for few-shot learning, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of visual concepts and interpretable models, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper also discusses the limitations of CNNs and proposes solutions, which could fall under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
